message: To get a good score (25-40 range), consistently combine a land animal, an air animal, and a water animal first. Once you have this 'amphibious flying' creature, apply *one* growth serum to it. Applying a second growth serum will decrease its value. The mutation catalyst seemed to cause negative values, so avoid it based on previous player's advice. The highest I achieved with this method was 40.

message: Always aim to craft an item that lives on land, in water, and in the air. Combine a land animal with a water animal first, then add an air animal. One 'growth serum' on this multi-habitat item usually provides a good value boost. Be cautious with a *second* 'growth serum'; it can sometimes decrease the value, especially if your initial components were 'large'. The 'mutation catalyst' was warned against by a previous player for leading to negative values, so I avoided it. I achieved consistent 40-45 scores by stopping after one or two growth serums on successful land+water+air combinations, submitting if the value wasn't increasing or started to drop.

A second growth serum will further increase the value to 45-50, *unless* any of the original components were 'large' (like giraffe or elephant). If there are 'large' components, only use one growth serum, as a second one will decrease the value. Avoid the 'mutation catalyst'; it always seems to result in negative values. Aim for items with a value of 45-50, which is the highest I achieved.
